 <body>
  <p>The email channel is one of the core channels in Adobe Campaign, allowing you to schedule and send personalized emails to specific targets.</p> 
  <p>You can send different types of emails:</p> 
  <ul>
   <li><p>Single-send emails: basic emails that you can send once to a defined target.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Recurring emails: send the same email regularly and aggregate each send and its reports on a periodic basis. A common example is a birthday email. Recurring emails are available through workflows only.</p> </li>
   <li><p>A/B testing emails: test up to 3 versions of an email.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Transactional emails: unitary emails that are triggered based on your customers' behavior. </p> </li>
  </ul>
  <p>To learn the best practices when creating and sending emails, consult the <a href="https://docs.campaign.adobe.com/doc/standard/getting_started/en/ACS_DeliveryBestPractices.html">Delivery best practices</a> step-by-step guide.</p> 
